-- Former Citi Co-Head of Leveraged Finance Julie Persily Said to Join Nomura
-- Kristen Haunss
-- 2010-07-12T22:00:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/former-citi-co-head-of-leveraged-finance-julie-persily-said-to-join-nomura.html

          
          
             Julie Persily , a former co-head of
U.S. leveraged finance at  Citigroup Inc. , has joined Nomura
Securities North America, a unit of Nomura Holdings Inc., in New
York as head of leveraged finance, according to people familiar
with the move.  
 Persily worked at Citigroup for nine years, joining from
Bankers Trust, where she also spent nine years, according to one
of the people.  
 Nomura has been building up its credit business in New York
and recently hired  Stephen Rielly  as head U.S. loan trader to
set up a sales and trading desk in New York for the Japanese
bank. It also hired salespeople  Nancy Broadbent  from Fortress
Investment Group LLC and  Jim Kelly  from Oppenheimer & Co.  
 Jonathan Hodgkinson , a Nomura spokesman, declined to
comment.  
